# UI Design System

## Visual Direction
Model every page after a modern marketplace aesthetic (Gumroad-style): clean white cards on a soft off-white background, content-first, minimal chrome. Light theme only for judge portal and public pages. Admin dashboard stays light too.

## Core Rules
- Background body: `bg-stone-100` or `bg-gray-50` — NEVER pure white on body
- Cards: `bg-white rounded-md border border-gray-200 flex flex-col`
- Card hover: `hover:shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,1)] transition-shadow duration-200`
- Primary accent color: `bg-pink-400` (buttons, badges, active states)
- Primary action buttons: `bg-black text-white` for CTAs
- NEVER use dark mode classes on public or judge pages
- NEVER use inline styles — Tailwind only

## Standard Card Pattern
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-md border border-gray-200 flex flex-col hover:shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,1)] transition-shadow duration-200">
  {/* Square thumbnail */}
  <div className="relative aspect-square">
    <img className="object-cover w-full h-full rounded-t-md" src={thumbnail} alt={title} />
  </div>
  {/* Content */}
  <div className="p-4 border-t border-gray-200 flex flex-col gap-3 flex-1">
    <h3 className="text-lg font-medium line-clamp-4">{title}</h3>
    {/* School row */}
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <div className="rounded-full border shrink-0 size-[16px] bg-gray-200" />
      <span className="text-sm font-medium underline">{schoolName}</span>
    </div>
    {/* Score row */}
    <div className="flex items-center gap-1">
      <StarIcon className="size-3.5" />
      <span className="text-sm font-medium">{score}</span>
    </div>
    {/* Category badge */}
    <div className="relative px-2 py-1 border bg-pink-400 w-fit text-sm font-medium rounded-sm">
      {category}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Typography Scale
- Page title: `text-2xl font-semibold` or `text-3xl font-bold`
- Card headline: `text-lg font-medium line-clamp-4`
- Section label: `text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700`
- Secondary/meta: `text-sm text-gray-500`
- Underlined links: `text-sm font-medium underline`

## Avatars & Icons
- Small avatars: `rounded-full border shrink-0 size-[16px]`
- Icon + text: `flex items-center gap-1` or `gap-2`
- Inline icons: `size-3.5`
- Button icons: `size-4`

## Badge / Pill Pattern
```tsx
<span className="relative px-2 py-1 border bg-pink-400 w-fit text-sm font-medium rounded-sm">
  {label}
</span>
```

## Navigation Tabs Pattern
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-2">
  <button className="rounded-full border border-black px-4 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-white">
    Active Tab
  </button>
  <button className="px-4 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-black">
    Inactive Tab
  </button>
</div>
```

## Layout Rules
- Page wrapper: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6`
- Card grids: `grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4`
- Stacked sections: `flex flex-col gap-4`
- Sidebar + content: `flex gap-6` with `w-64 shrink-0` sidebar
- Filter rows: `flex items-center gap-2`

## Page-Specific Rules

### Submission Form (/submit/[eventId])
- Centered: `max-w-2xl mx-auto`
- File upload zone: `border-dashed border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-md p-8 text-center`
- Submit button: `w-full bg-pink-400 hover:bg-pink-500 text-white font-medium py-3 rounded-md`

### Judge Portal (/judge/**)
- Mobile-first — single column on mobile, 2-col on tablet: `grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4`
- Score sliders: `h-2 accent-pink-400` — large and touch-friendly
- Score total badge: large and prominent, `text-4xl font-bold text-pink-400`

### Stat Cards (Dashboard)
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-md border border-gray-200 p-4 flex flex-col gap-1">
  <span className="text-sm text-gray-500">{label}</span>
  <span className="text-3xl font-bold">{value}</span>
  <span className="text-xs text-gray-400">{sub}</span>
</div>
```

## Component Rules
- Always use `cn()` from lib/utils for conditional classNames
- Import shadcn components from `@/components/ui/`
- Never build a custom input/button/dialog from scratch — always use shadcn first
- Lucide icons only — no other icon libraries
